items.name: IronCatFateToon
items.description:
IronCatFateToon

Making models is a thing I do for fun. So if you like what I do? You can help me out by just using the model and leaving a review!

IronCatFateToon's goal is to be able to create nice looking anime style images with vibrant colours, more simplistic anime (cartoony) colour/style look and with influence of Fate/Stay Night: Unlimited Blade Works styling.

This checkpoint requires a VAE, I recommend kl-f8-anime2, I've also used it for the examples. Edit: Since the original upload of this checkpoint, I've updated v1.0 itself and reuploaded the checkpoint with the VAE baked in. If you prefer the checkpoint without it baked in, download the v1.0-no-vae version.

In order to achieve what's just been promised I used MeinaMix V8 as the base checkpoint, I then merged two of my style LoRA's into MeinaMix V8; Anime vibrancy & simplifier Style (Merge ratio of 0.4`) & Fate/stay night: UBW Style (Merge ratio of 0.6`) . And finally I merged the result of that with the checkpoint Mistoon_Anime. Where I did a weighted merge, 70% was used from the results of me merging the LoRA's into MeinaMix V8. And 30% was used for Mistoon_Anime. (Note: I didn't use the exact same Anime vibrancy & simplifier Style LoRA when merging, I retrained on the same dataset from that LoRA for a more nuanced look that complimented MeinaMix V8 better i.m.o.)

Some things you might recognize from Fate/stay night: UBW in this checkpoint, is in the way how eyes, scenery, city, cityscape, sky, grass, trees, certain 2.5D angles et cetera are generated. The anime/cartoony look is a combination from my Anime vibrancy & simplifier Style LoRA and Mistoon_Anime. While MeinaMix V8 as a base gives in my own opinion a really sollid base for good looking art.

I haven't used any embeddings in the example images so you should get a good idea, in what the checkpoint can create on its own. I generated the images using some wildcard libraries, so the prompts might sometimes seem random.

Advice:

  • I would recommended a clip skip of 2

  • I personally like lollypop as an upscaler a lot, it gives anime images a nice soft upscaled touch.

  • I am personally a fan of using DPM++ SDE Karras with 15 steps and when Hires fixing, I like to use 10 for Hires steps and a denoise of about 0.35 or 0.4. Most example images use 512x768 as base resolution.

  • If you want the same vibrant, high contrast style look from my images you've seen, mostly in the images with girls, I suggest the following starter prompt: (masterpiece, best quality:1.4), cinematic light, colorful, high contrast, the prompt cinematic light is optional but I've used it in most of the example images since I liked the look. The high contrast prompt may sometimes do bad in certain NSFW generations, if you notice it in a seed you can try to remove it.

    • The starter prompt is not necessarily needed, I also included 2 examples where I just typed out a story based prompt and only used the negative prompt like below. And those images also came out great i.m.o.

  • I would advice the following starter negative prompt in general to get the look you see in most of my example images: (worst quality:1.2), (low quality:1.2), (lowres:1.1), (monochrome:1.1), (greyscale), multiple views, comic, sketch. You can also use my full negative prompt from my sample images, if you liked the look of them.

    • The bad-artist negative embedding seems to work pretty nice too, which you can try instead of my suggested negative prompt.

This model wouldn't have been possible without these awesome creators:

  • @Meina for MeinaMix V8

  • @Inzaniak for Mistoon_Anime

  • hakurei for kl-f8-anime2

训练素材使用动漫截图80张，生成后能高度还原动漫画风，但风格太过于固定，使用分层融合方法能有效去风格化。但冰狼爪很难训练，最终效果非常差，于是我在训练集中去除了该部分内容，现在就是尽可能还原特征并去风格化的模型，效果可以参考我的测试图。触发词ANIMAL FOOT,FOX GIRL,white hair,

刹那有两种发型，分别使用用关键词："twin tails" 和 "long hair"如果不生效，请提高权重

The training material consists of 80 screenshots from anime, which can highly restore the anime style after generation. However, the style is too fixed, and using a layered fusion method can effectively de-style the images. However, it's difficult to train the ice wolf claw, and the final effect is very poor, so I removed that part from the training set. Now, the model aims to restore features as much as possible while removing the style, and the effect can be seen in my test images. The trigger words are "ANIMAL FOOT", "FOX GIRL", "white hair".

Setsuna has two hairstyles, one with twin tails and the other with long hair, respectively identified by the keywords "twin tails" and "long hair".If it doesn't work, please increase the weight.

items.name: NaviGavi / seojh1029 Style
items.description:
A style LoRA sporting vivid colors and solid support to make all kinds of characters.

How to use
Use trigger tag "navigavistyle" and then just prompt away.
This LoRA came out surprisingly stable and can produce high quality results even on plain old NAI so all sample images are from it. If you're out of inspiration you can even prompt just "1girl" or "1boy" and generally get something decent out of it.
That said due to the large dataset no manual cleaning has been done so you may, rarely, see stray text or more characters than you prompted for.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

Misc
Trained on NAI. Dataset of 200 images.
All images are untouched raw txt2imgs, no inpainting done, for quality transparency.

items.name: Fortnite Dolph
items.description:
If you make some cool images, please consider sharing them. That is why I make these. :)

I am the Reindeer Czar, so I created my first LORA, of Dolph from Fortnite. This depicts him really well I think.

Latest Description:

Version 2 improves the model very much. No more issue with background, overall more expressive and high quality. 0.5 - 0.7 weight for LORA is good. Euler a and DPM++ seem to be best sampling. Sample around 50 seems good too, more can be better too.

You can add tags like skydiving, sitting, open mouth, smiling, holding weapon, lightsaber to use for some dynamic situations. You can also add Widow's Promise, Sword to get that back bling on him.

If you like my models, please consider a tip, to help me train more models!

https://ko-fi.com/reindeerczar

Deprecated Version 1 Description:

Strength for LORA is say, 0.4 to 0.65 to get the good result, if you want a b1ackground.

It was trained on 5600 iterations, so quite much. Add the tags blue gradient background and simple background in the negative tag to get rid of the background better.

modelVersions.name: v3.3
modelVersions.description:
New version, re-trained a few times, after I was told it was overtrained!!!

Still new to LoRa, but getting it dialed in, I think. :)

I like Heun sampling for this one. I did not bake in a vae, so feel free to add one you like, if the image is desaturated. I have been using vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors.

The colour looks nice with that one.

You can use 3/4 Rear View, and Rear View, to get back views of Dolph. His back strappy things should be rendered correctly now. I did not tag rear view last time, so it should be cleaner.

Nothing really new, just seems to not blow out the model, and the result image is much nicer. Post your feedback and pictures! :D

items.name: Artoria Lancer Alter | Fate/Grand Order (FGO)
items.description:
The tags I use the most - 1girl, artoria pendragon \(lancer alter\) \(fate\), large (or huge) breasts, wide hips, blond hair, yellow eyes.

For normal outfit - large breasts, underboob, ribbed_leotard, black clothes,

For Royal Icing (Or something that looks like royal Icing) - white negligee, lingerie, black_stockings.

First attempt at making a Lora. Trained on 666 images of - pay close attention! Artoria Pendragon Lancer Alter PLUS everything that had her tag. That means most of the images with Royal Icing outfit. It means that hypothetically you can make something close to Royal Icing with other characters at slightly lower weights.

Using this lora on high weights will eventually lead to features unique to Artoria (The headwear and maybe the face thing). And, honestly, I still don't know which one of the epochs to upload because it was trained on 3300 steps with 1 repeat and 2 batch sizes, which I was told is overtrained. However, I ran a few tests with epoch 10 (out of 10, the most trained one), and the results were mostly fine. Images are done with MeinaHentai.

Also, higher weight for the most part - I believe- makes skimpier outfits.

Again, that's first LORA, I'm not sure how to properly run tests to determine if it's fine or not, because so far epochs got me everything I needed.
